def_cn: （旧时的）满师学徒工，学徒期满的工匠
def_en: In former times, a journeyman was a worker who had finished learning a trade and who was employed by someone rather than working on his or her own.

def_cn: （缺乏天分或原创性的）熟练工，熟手
def_en: If you refer to someone as a journeyman, you mean that they have the basic skill which their job requires, but are not very talented or original.
